<p>
  <span class="nym">Justus</span>
  <span class="gen">m.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Latin</span> <i>justus</i> 'just, fair'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The byname of a Biblical character who was later venerated as a saint, a 2nd C pope and saint, a semi-legendary 3rd C saint, two 4th C martyrs, a 4th C French saint, and a 6th C Spanish saint. Wycliffite Bible (1395): <i>Just</i>.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>This name is sometimes conflated with <a class="nym" href="Josse">Josse</a>, via spellings such as <i>Jost</i>.</p>
  
  


